Invoicing Staff
Responsibilities
PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIESAchievement of DSO result as yearly DSO BudgetGenerate invoicing to local or international customers and SGS affiliates. REPORTING LINEAdministration Manager SPECIFIC RESPONSIBILITIESCollection:To collect all outstanding invoices starting from over 360days to below.Collection efficiency should reach >60% on weekly basis.To update result of collection in A/R Finance folder.To record proof payment received from customers in the job files or CTS ServerReport the result of collection on weekly basis to Administration Manager.Invoicing:Prepare & issuance invoice to local, International customers & SGS affiliates.1% tolerance per year of credit note issuance.To report weekly revenue to Administration Manager.Any other duties requested by the Administration Coordinator, Administration Manager, or Delegate. PROFILE Bachelor Degree (Related Field) or equivalent, orTwo years experience in a similar position. REQUIRED SKILLS Good communication skills and interface with Customers.Understanding of with holding tax calculation.Good organizational skills and able work un supervised.
